text: Diana Box Alonso (born 6 March 1971) is a Spanish team handball player who played for the club CBF Elda and on the Spanish national team. She was born in Haute-Savoie, France. She competed at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens, where the Spanish team made the quarter-finals.Profile: Diana Box sports- reference.com (Retrieved on 24 January 2014) ==References== Category:1971 births Category:Living people Category:People from Haute-Savoie Category:Spanish handball players Category:Olympic handball players for Spain Category:Handball players at the 2004 Summer Olympics
